title: For Sale:  Nickle Colt Python 357
postcontent: 1976 Rare Colt Python Nickle 38/357 with Genuine Mother of Pearl grips with gold Colt medallions, factory Pachmyre grips with gold Colt medallions and a Walnut french fit Custom Shop case ( Very nice and completely custom to this gun ) with a nickle plated Colt three way screw driver Colt letter, warranty card and a manual.  This Python is in excellent condition. Serial number 454XXE, born in 1976 another bicentennial gun. There is one small nick on the bottom of the crane an shown in the pictures. A little history on the Python; The Python was created by adding a full under lug vent rib barrel and precision adjustable sights to Colt’s venerable “I” frame in 1955, the same frame used for the .38 Special Official Police and the .357 Magnum Trooper. The Python was precision made and hand fitted and was essentially a mass produced custom gun. It was intended as a precision target revolver, but law enforcement and the public at large fell in love with the Big Snake. There were blued models, .38 Special only Target Models with eight-inch barrels, high polish nickel models and the one I lusted after, a high polish stainless steel model. Colt produced the Python as a regular production item until 2000,and as a custom shop special order item until 2003. And there will never be another Python. Oh, if Colt’s management were to pull their collective heads out of their collective fourth points of contact and realize the the company can’t survive on dwindling military contracts and civilian sales of their existing lineup, there might be a revolver with “Python” on the barrel. But it won’t be a real Python.Lots more pictures available upon request.  Sorry coukd only post 5.

title: For Sale:  FN FS2000 (Less Than 300 Rounds Through This Gun = Safe Queen!) Not Imported Into US Anymore!
postcontent: Click Here To View This FN FS2000 On Our Website Fabrique Nationale, through its U.S. subsidiary FNH-USA, manufactures one of the most modern, innovative and frankly atypical applications of the "bullpup" design in its FS2000 rifle-a semi-automatic-only variant of the company's F2000 select-fire rifle. Chambered in 5.56x45 mm (.223 Rem.) and designed to feed from AR-15/M16 magazines, the gas piston-driven FS2000 was first introduced to the U.S. market in 2006.     The FS2000 Standard features modern materials and manufacture, with a tough polymer stock and an aluminum receiver. The rifle's bolt, barrel and a barrel-extension into which the bolt locks are all steel. The 171⁄2-inch barrel has a 1:7 rate-of-twist and features a permanently attached muzzle brake. A modular fire-control assembly, made primarily of polymer, is located inside the butt of rifle's stock and is easily removable.   One of the most unique qualities of the FS2000 is it's almost entirely ambidextrous. An Achilles' heel of most bullpup designs-particularly for southpaws-is having the action of the rifle located behind the trigger, the ejection port is then in the rifle's buttstock near the shooter's face. FN's solution was novel-a forward ejection system that employs a tube above the barrel and an ejection port on the upper right side of the receiver, covered by a hinged synthetic door.    Another unique feature of the FS2000 is its inspection cover door located to the rear of the optics cover assembly.
